.content
  %section.intro
    .width
      %h2 What is the Portland Code School?
      %p The Portland Code School is an intensive 12-week course focused on teaching the essential skills necessary to begin working as a junior programmer upon graduation.
      %p Our students are smart, creative, passionate, super-rad people who want to learn code and jump-start a career in web development.

  %section.announcements

  %section.accolades
    .statements
      %h2 What people are saying about PCS
      %article
        .img_wrap
          %img{:src => "/images/students/pete.jpg"}
        .quote
          %p For me, the Portland Code School has been an awesome experience. The program of study covered a broad range of skills that I continue to use daily.  Our instructor, Chuck, not only draws from both a broad and deep knowledge-base, but communicates it well.
          .meta
            %strong Pete Kinnecom
            %p.company Developer at Appfolio
      %article
        .img_wrap
          %img{:src => "/images/students/rachel.jpg"}
        .quote
          %p Portland Code School has equipped me with the tools to continue growing as a developer. The highlights for me were the camaraderie among the students and those moments when I realized how far I'd come.
          .meta
            %strong Rachel Sakry
            %p.company Developer at Elemental Technologies
      %article.last
        .img_wrap
          %img{:src => "/images/bill.jpg"}
        .quote
          %p Chuck is a great resource for anyone learning Ruby and Rails.  He is an enthusiastic teacher and has a broad knowledge of the subject.  I enthusiastically recommend Chuck and the Portland Code School.
          .meta
            %strong Bill Den Beste
            %p.company Owner of Reprise Inc. and ChickTech mentor

